1-3-4v-3h15v4c0%203%200%203-3%203-2%200-2%200-2%206l1%207h12v-6c0-6%200-7-2-7s-2-1-3-4v-3h15v4c0%202%200%203-2%203s-2%201-2%207v6h9v-10c-1-15%200-13-11-13h-8v-5c0-4%200-5%202-5s2-1%202-7v-6h-6l-6%201M55%20176c-4%204-2%2010%204%2010%205%200%207-7%203-10-2-3-5-2-7%200m61%200c-4%204-2%209%203%2010%205%202%208-7%204-10-2-3-5-2-7%200m169%2035c-3%204-1%2010%202%2010l3%202%202%201v-1c-1-1%200-2%201-3%201-3%201-7-1-9-2-3-6-2-7%200'%20fill='%23d3d3d3'%20fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","aspectRatio":1.9230769230769231,"src":"/static/49ab9e05b3c84b077874c20a77f5a58b/5d2c5/banner.png","srcSet":"/static/49ab9e05b3c84b077874c20a77f5a58b/002c1/banner.png 250w,\n/static/49ab9e05b3c84b077874c20a77f5a58b/53f65/banner.png 500w,\n/static/49ab9e05b3c84b077874c20a77f5a58b/5d2c5/banner.png 1000w,\n/static/49ab9e05b3c84b077874c20a77f5a58b/8d364/banner.png 1500w,\n/static/49ab9e05b3c84b077874c20a77f5a58b/3ba25/banner.png 2000w,\n/static/49ab9e05b3c84b077874c20a77f5a58b/9a9ee/banner.png 2084w","sizes":"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"}}}}},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":".NET Core","slug":"netcore"}]}}]}},"wpPost":{"title":"ASP.NET Core 2.2 Authorizations using Policy with Requirement based on AD groups","content":"\n<h2>Background</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>On ASP.NET Core applications, authorizations are configure on Startup at <em>ConfigureServices </em>method.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So in a simple case of authorization, we can use something like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1603 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:767px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:22.395833333333332%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAAECAIAAAABPYjBAAAACXBIWXMAAA7DAAAOwwHHb6hkAAAAhklEQVQI15WOyxLDIAhF/f8vbaIgGIgGJSntupueYe5cYHgkKFarI57b9so5A8C27wUAEZm5tSN0zvn8IvmajStTzaUgAhMxgFCNgfuLu4c3s2nzNov8jtZ1rbVS+N67ip6qxDxEn9YionKIqGpcpg98EDmzjyt01tpVUyyIrojEn2OM5x/eyQbn5wj8gDEAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/8c831/1.png 192w,\n/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/643d6/1.png 384w,\n/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/2059a/1.png 767w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 100vw, 767px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 100vw, 767px\" srcSet=\"/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/8c831/1.png 192w,\n/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/643d6/1.png 384w,\n/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/2059a/1.png 767w\" src=\"/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/2059a/1.png\" alt=\".net core configure services\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/8c831/1.png 192w,\n/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/643d6/1.png 384w,\n/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/2059a/1.png 767w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 100vw, 767px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 100vw, 767px\" srcset=\"/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/8c831/1.png 192w,\n/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/643d6/1.png 384w,\n/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/2059a/1.png 767w\" src=\"/static/759dae042600f47c3c83434485dbaf05/2059a/1.png\" alt=\".net core configure services\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But, if you have the case you need more than one claim to access the same resource,  controller for instance, you´ll need to add another require claim to the same policy. This will get you on a <strong>AND</strong> scenario. This means that <strong>ALL</strong> <em>RequireClaim </em>must be fulfill by the user in context. As a result, this scenario may not be your goal. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the perfect scenario, we need the <strong>OR</strong> scenario to be in consideration, i.e., at least one <em>RequireClaim </em>should be enough to authorize the user in context.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This can\nbe accomplished with Authorization Requirements and Handlers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Scenario</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You have more than one AD group that should access to the same resource on your application. Different users belong to different AD groups and all this users need access to the named resource. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the authorization pipeline, we need to validate the user context against all authorized AD groups. This means, if the user in context is in at least one of the AD groups, it should be enough to authorize and give access to the resource.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Solution<strong> </strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Main Setup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Making use of Requirement and Handlers available on ASP.NET Core 2.2, you can now dive into a <strong>OR</strong> scenario. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This solution is based on ASP.NET Core 2.2 with windows authentication in witch, there is a <em>MyFeatureController </em>we want to protect. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simple put, we create a <strong>Requirement </strong>like this: </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1604 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:453px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:44.247787610619476%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/361f3/2.png 113w,\n/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/caac3/2.png 227w,\n/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/7b460/2.png 453w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 453px) 100vw, 453px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 453px) 100vw, 453px\" srcSet=\"/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/361f3/2.png 113w,\n/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/caac3/2.png 227w,\n/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/7b460/2.png 453w\" src=\"/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/7b460/2.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/361f3/2.png 113w,\n/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/caac3/2.png 227w,\n/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/7b460/2.png 453w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 453px) 100vw, 453px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 453px) 100vw, 453px\" srcset=\"/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/361f3/2.png 113w,\n/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/caac3/2.png 227w,\n/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/7b460/2.png 453w\" src=\"/static/078679dbaf6cf2439237ee42e4a79794/7b460/2.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And then an <strong>Handler </strong>to… you know… handle the requirement. In this case, we are handling/validating a list of AD groups against the user context. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Handler code looks like this: </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1649 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:730px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:79.78142076502733%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/c82e3/3-2.png 183w,\n/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/02681/3-2.png 365w,\n/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/2d0a6/3-2.png 730w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" srcSet=\"/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/c82e3/3-2.png 183w,\n/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/02681/3-2.png 365w,\n/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/2d0a6/3-2.png 730w\" src=\"/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/2d0a6/3-2.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/c82e3/3-2.png 183w,\n/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/02681/3-2.png 365w,\n/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/2d0a6/3-2.png 730w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" srcset=\"/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/c82e3/3-2.png 183w,\n/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/02681/3-2.png 365w,\n/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/2d0a6/3-2.png 730w\" src=\"/static/924641ede86fa94984e6a9f303c5a2a9/2d0a6/3-2.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next step is to use the both above classes, as base classes to <em>MyFeature </em><strong>Requirement </strong>and <strong>Handler</strong> classes: </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1606 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:519px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:38.46153846153846%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/3fa95/4.png 130w,\n/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/1d4e6/4.png 260w,\n/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/572de/4.png 519w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 519px) 100vw, 519px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 519px) 100vw, 519px\" srcSet=\"/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/3fa95/4.png 130w,\n/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/1d4e6/4.png 260w,\n/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/572de/4.png 519w\" src=\"/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/572de/4.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/3fa95/4.png 130w,\n/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/1d4e6/4.png 260w,\n/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/572de/4.png 519w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 519px) 100vw, 519px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 519px) 100vw, 519px\" srcset=\"/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/3fa95/4.png 130w,\n/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/1d4e6/4.png 260w,\n/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/572de/4.png 519w\" src=\"/static/cc3a6e7c4fd14795a8a61e500631bfad/572de/4.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1607 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:521px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:23.846153846153847%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/3fa95/5.png 130w,\n/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/c747f/5.png 261w,\n/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/ab3ab/5.png 521w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 521px) 100vw, 521px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 521px) 100vw, 521px\" srcSet=\"/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/3fa95/5.png 130w,\n/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/c747f/5.png 261w,\n/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/ab3ab/5.png 521w\" src=\"/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/ab3ab/5.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/3fa95/5.png 130w,\n/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/c747f/5.png 261w,\n/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/ab3ab/5.png 521w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 521px) 100vw, 521px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 521px) 100vw, 521px\" srcset=\"/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/3fa95/5.png 130w,\n/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/c747f/5.png 261w,\n/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/ab3ab/5.png 521w\" src=\"/static/136785cf1ee367392778ee8b8b8f87dd/ab3ab/5.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, the\nonly big step missing, is the configuration on startup.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To do this, first, we need to add the list of AD groups authorized to access the <em>MyFeatureController </em>on the <em>appsettings.json</em>:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1608 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:220px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:58.18181818181818%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/e5051/6.png 55w,\n/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/707e9/6.png 110w,\n/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/d42a7/6.png 220w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 220px) 100vw, 220px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 220px) 100vw, 220px\" srcSet=\"/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/e5051/6.png 55w,\n/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/707e9/6.png 110w,\n/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/d42a7/6.png 220w\" src=\"/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/d42a7/6.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/e5051/6.png 55w,\n/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/707e9/6.png 110w,\n/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/d42a7/6.png 220w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 220px) 100vw, 220px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 220px) 100vw, 220px\" srcset=\"/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/e5051/6.png 55w,\n/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/707e9/6.png 110w,\n/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/d42a7/6.png 220w\" src=\"/static/3c7fdd1bbc920d4648eb54d75833df43/d42a7/6.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And then, configure the authorization service on <em>ConfigureServices </em>at Startup: </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1648 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:566px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:41.54929577464789%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/efde3/7-3.png 142w,\n/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/26fa5/7-3.png 283w,\n/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/fa6a1/7-3.png 566w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 566px) 100vw, 566px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 566px) 100vw, 566px\" srcSet=\"/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/efde3/7-3.png 142w,\n/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/26fa5/7-3.png 283w,\n/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/fa6a1/7-3.png 566w\" src=\"/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/fa6a1/7-3.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/efde3/7-3.png 142w,\n/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/26fa5/7-3.png 283w,\n/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/fa6a1/7-3.png 566w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 566px) 100vw, 566px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 566px) 100vw, 566px\" srcset=\"/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/efde3/7-3.png 142w,\n/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/26fa5/7-3.png 283w,\n/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/fa6a1/7-3.png 566w\" src=\"/static/d7c3101a28223a798275c418460c6d18/fa6a1/7-3.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After all this setup, we create a custom <em>AuthorizeAttribute </em>with <em>MyFeature </em>Policy. Then we&#8217;re good to go to use it on <em>MyFeatureController</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1610 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:536px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:25.37313432835821%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/98c58/8.png 134w,\n/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/471d4/8.png 268w,\n/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/56468/8.png 536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 536px) 100vw, 536px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 536px) 100vw, 536px\" srcSet=\"/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/98c58/8.png 134w,\n/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/471d4/8.png 268w,\n/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/56468/8.png 536w\" src=\"/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/56468/8.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/98c58/8.png 134w,\n/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/471d4/8.png 268w,\n/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/56468/8.png 536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 536px) 100vw, 536px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 536px) 100vw, 536px\" srcset=\"/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/98c58/8.png 134w,\n/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/471d4/8.png 268w,\n/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/56468/8.png 536w\" src=\"/static/8f2f70bbf89769fa067b10c752447277/56468/8.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1611 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:458px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:40.869565217391305%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/a22de/9.png 115w,\n/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/ccc33/9.png 229w,\n/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/e9a79/9.png 458w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 458px) 100vw, 458px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 458px) 100vw, 458px\" srcSet=\"/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/a22de/9.png 115w,\n/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/ccc33/9.png 229w,\n/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/e9a79/9.png 458w\" src=\"/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/e9a79/9.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/a22de/9.png 115w,\n/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/ccc33/9.png 229w,\n/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/e9a79/9.png 458w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 458px) 100vw, 458px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 458px) 100vw, 458px\" srcset=\"/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/a22de/9.png 115w,\n/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/ccc33/9.png 229w,\n/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/e9a79/9.png 458w\" src=\"/static/8606c5d886cec71c5ee83a09483bb5a7/e9a79/9.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>View Usage</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Since we added our policy to the Authorization pipeline, we can also use this on razor pages to show/hide features based on user authorizations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Firstly, we have to inject the <em>AuthorizationService </em>into the Views Engine, and to accomplish this, we need to add this 3 lines in the file <em>_ViewImports.cshtml</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1612 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:436px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:14.678899082568808%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/d8a37/10.png 109w,\n/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/1a647/10.png 218w,\n/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/e7d53/10.png 436w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 436px) 100vw, 436px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 436px) 100vw, 436px\" srcSet=\"/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/d8a37/10.png 109w,\n/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/1a647/10.png 218w,\n/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/e7d53/10.png 436w\" src=\"/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/e7d53/10.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/d8a37/10.png 109w,\n/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/1a647/10.png 218w,\n/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/e7d53/10.png 436w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 436px) 100vw, 436px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 436px) 100vw, 436px\" srcset=\"/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/d8a37/10.png 109w,\n/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/1a647/10.png 218w,\n/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/e7d53/10.png 436w\" src=\"/static/82699308c35439b77d5cb707c0682db3/e7d53/10.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Secondly, we can now use the <em>AuthorizationService</em> control what to render on views. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, we added the below code on the<em> index.cshtml</em> of Home:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"wp-image-1613 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:731px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:28.415300546448087%\"></span><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/c82e3/11.png 183w,\n/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/6cd33/11.png 366w,\n/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/9f2f1/11.png 731w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 731px) 100vw, 731px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 731px) 100vw, 731px\" srcSet=\"/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/c82e3/11.png 183w,\n/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/6cd33/11.png 366w,\n/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/9f2f1/11.png 731w\" src=\"/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/9f2f1/11.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/c82e3/11.png 183w,\n/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/6cd33/11.png 366w,\n/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/9f2f1/11.png 731w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 731px) 100vw, 731px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 731px) 100vw, 731px\" srcset=\"/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/c82e3/11.png 183w,\n/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/6cd33/11.png 366w,\n/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/9f2f1/11.png 731w\" src=\"/static/1d430cfd02789a4bef6c8d31e9d2d136/9f2f1/11.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span><figcaption>Authorization Service in use at razor page<br></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, with <strong>Requirement </strong>and <strong>Handler</strong>, we have a lot of flexibility of how we want to authorize our application resources. In this case, we are using windows authentication and AD groups to authorize user access, but, it can be easily other kind of authorization to fulfill your needs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can check the full example at github:</p>\n\n\n\n<p> <a href=\"https://github.com/devscopeninjas/asp-net-core-2-authorization-requirement\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/devscopeninjas/asp-net-core-2-authorization-requirement</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Resources</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://odetocode.com/blogs/scott/archive/2018/02/20/role-based-authorization-in-asp-net-core-with-azure-ad.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://odetocode.com/blogs/scott/archive/2018/02/20/role-based-authorization-in-asp-net-core-with-azure-ad.aspx</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/security/authorization/policies?view=aspnetcore-2.2#requirements\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/security/authorization/policies?view=aspnetcore-2.2#requirements</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/security/authorization/iauthorizationpolicyprovider?view=aspnetcore-2.2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/security/authorization/iauthorizationpolicyprovider?view=aspnetcore-2.2</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/security/authorization/views?view=aspnetcore-2.2&amp;tabs=aspnetcore2x\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/security/authorization/views?view=aspnetcore-2.2&amp;tabs=aspnetcore2x</a></p>\n","excerpt":"<p>Background On ASP.NET Core applications, authorizations are configure on Startup at ConfigureServices method. So in a simple case of authorization, we can use something like this: But, if you have the case you need more than one claim to access the same resource, controller for instance, you´ll need to add another require claim to the&hellip; <a class=\"more-link\" href=\"/asp-net-core-2-2-authorization/\">Continue reading <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">ASP.NET Core 2.2 Authorizations using Policy with Requirement based on AD groups</span></a></p>\n","date":"March 15, 2019","modified":"March 15, 2019","author":{"node":{"id":"dXNlcjox","name":"admin","url":null,"description":null,"slug":"admin"}},"slug":"asp-net-core-2-2-authorization","id":"cG9zdDoxNjAw","featuredImage":{"node":{"altText":"ASP.NET Core Authorization","localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='360'%20height='240'%20viewBox='0%200%20360%20240'%20preserveAspectRatio='none'%3e%3cpath%20d='M0%2021l1%2020%201%201H1l-1%2099v99h361V0H0v21m110%2053v59h153V47H110v27m45-22l31%201c27%200%2032%200%2032-2l-31-1c-30%200-32%200-32%202m13%205c0%202%201%202%2019%202%2017%200%2018%200%2018-2s-1-2-18-2c-18%200-19%200-19%202m-37%2018v12h67l-1-12V63h-66v12m24%2023v7h19V90h-19v8m67%2017v8h19v-15l-9-1h-10v8m111-5c-2%201-3%207-1%209l4%201c4%200%205-2%205-6%200-6-5-8-8-4m-313%208c-4%202-6%206-6%2012%200%205%200%206-2%207-